T1  - Financial Contracting Under Imperfect Enforcement*
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjq006
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 126
IS  - 1
SP  - 323
EP  - 371
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We develop a model of financial contracting under imperfect enforcement. Financial contracts are designed to keep entrepreneurs from diverting project returns, but enforcement is probabilistic and penalties are limited. The model rationalizes the prevalence of straight debt and common stock, and its predictions are consistent with a host of empirical capital structure regularities.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjq006
ER  - 



